name: Adam Robinson
text:
Just moved here in august and was and am looking for a family dr to write all my scripts instead of going to a family dr and pain clinic
Every month. So i went to see several drs in the area and one dr wrote me suboxone which is way too much and when I called him back and ask him to change the medicine he refused. So I dropped him. I have seen a neurologist and a neurosurgeon as well and seeing my previous pain doctor that's 3 hours away. my regular pain doctor wrote my scripts I trashed the Suboxone and ask my neurosurgeon to write my Percocet and he did. So I see doctor lamberson. Nice guy,  nice staff, but doubt ill go again because from the time he walked in the room I could tell he was looking at me like an addict. And when I told him why I wasn't there he started questioning my prescriptions. He pulled off the printer of all my previous prescriptions I've had filled and said I've seen too many doctors. Even though he saw I only use two doctors in the past 4 years he only paid attention two the few doctors I've seen since moving here. I told him that I was trying to find one doctor to write all my prescriptions and that's why there's several doctors write my prescriptions lately. so I left there with no prescriptions and now the search continues  for a doctor as caring as my other doctor was before moving here. I know it looks like I'm Doctor shopping and I guess I am still looking  for not only a pain doctor but a family doctor.
